# Private environment exposed to the agent on every task run.
# The coordinator copies this file (when present, named `.agent.env`) into
# each tasks/<task_id>/.env before spawning OpenCode, so the agent can:
#   - source it from bash:  `source .env && echo "$HOPSWORKS_PROJECT"`
#   - load it from Python:  `from dotenv import load_dotenv; load_dotenv()`
#
# Put any credentials or project pointers the agent needs here.
# Keep it OUT of git (gitignored). It's separate from the testbed's `.env`
# (which holds ANTHROPIC_API_KEY / KAGGLE_KEY for the harness, not the agent).

# HOPSWORKS_API_KEY=
# HOPSWORKS_PROJECT=
# HOPSWORKS_HOST=
